1. Garbage collection in Java is the automated process of deleting code that's no longer needed or used.
OR
2. Garbage collection automatic memory management process in java. Object without reference or unused objects
that's no longer needed or used is deleted.

3. This automatically frees up memory space and make JAVA an efficient language
4. Garbage collection works on heap memory.
5. Garbage collector in java runs on Daemon thread.

6. Daemon thread in Java is a service provider thread that provides services to the user thread.
Its life depends on the mercy of user threads i.e. when all the user threads die,
JVM terminates this thread automatically.
There are many Daemon threads in java running automatically e.g. gc, finalizer, etc.




